.TH RAMSTEIND 8 "2026-07-17" "ramstein 0.5.0" "ramstein manual"
.SH NAME
ramsteind \- the ramstein memory daemon
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ramsteind
.RB [ \-\-config
.IR path ]
.RB [ \-\-once ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B ramsteind
is the only privileged actor in ramstein: it owns the truth about bytes
alive \(em
.IR /proc/meminfo " + " /proc/pressure/memory
polling, EWMA burn rate, ETA-to-OOM, a per-process sqlite index, and the
gentle (and one ungentle) levers
.BR ramstein (1)'s
.I calm
verb acts through. Nothing above the control socket ever needs privilege
to read; writing (cgroup
.IR memory.high ,
renice, kill) does.
.PP
.B \-\-once
performs a single poll, writes
.IR status.json ,
and exits \(em used by
.B make smoke
and testing.
.SH CONFIGURATION
Config is the seed, never the master: every key is typed and clamped on
load; unknown keys are ignored; a tampered config can tune numbers within
the ranges below but can never grant the daemon a new ability or weaken
an invariant \(em the kill gate, the coexistence check, and the memory.high
RSS floor are hardcoded, not configurable. Default path:
.IR /etc/ramstein/config.json .
.TS
tab(@) allbox;
lb lb lb
l l l.
key@default@clamp
poll_interval@10@1\(en3600
burn_tau@120@5\(en86400
eta_cap_hours@24.0@0.1\(en8760
warn_psi_some@10.0@0\(en100
warn_avail_pct@15.0@0\(en100
warn_eta_hours@4.0@0.01\(en8760
hot_psi_full@5.0@0\(en100
hot_avail_pct@5.0@0\(en100
hot_eta_minutes@30.0@0.1\(en525600
owner_uid@1000@0\(en2^31
sample_every@3@1\(en360
proc_min_bytes@16MiB@1MiB\(en2^40
recent_ring@120@2\(en100000
hourly_ring@168@2\(en100000
advise_growth_mib_per_hour@500.0@1\(en1000000
.TE
.PP
Units are seconds unless named otherwise.
.I sample_every
is poll ticks between M2 samples;
.I proc_min_bytes
is the rss+swap floor a process must clear to earn an index row;
.I recent_ring
/
.I hourly_ring
are sample counts kept in each ring;
.I advise_growth_mib_per_hour
is rule 2's leak-ish growth-rate threshold.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /etc/ramstein/config.json
Seeded once at install (owner_uid from the installing sudo call), never
overwritten on reinstall.
.TP
.I /var/lib/ramstein/index.db
The per-process sample ring (sqlite, WAL mode): two rings sharing one
promoted flag \(em
.I recent_ring
keeps every sample (~1h at defaults),
.I hourly_ring
keeps one promoted sample per hour (~7d). Identity key is
.RI ( pid ", " starttime )
so a reused pid can never be mistaken for the process that held it before.
.TP
.I /var/lib/ramstein/ledger.jsonl
One JSON line per
.I calm
or
.I kill
action: timestamp, verb, pid, comm, argument, result.
.TP
.I /run/ramstein/status.json
0640, owned by
.IR owner_uid .
Written atomically (tmp file + rename). Carries the M2/M3 pill digest
(top process, zombie count, one advise headline) for the GNOME extension,
recomputed on the sampler's own cadence.
.TP
.I /run/ramstein/control.sock
0660, owned by
.IR owner_uid .
.SH SIGNALS
.TP
.B SIGTERM, SIGINT
Clean shutdown: the current poll loop iteration finishes, the socket is
closed.
.SH SECURITY
The relevant attacker is an unprivileged local process abusing the root
daemon; ramsteind has no network attack surface at all \(em the only
component that ever reaches the internet is the separate, unprivileged
.BR ramstein\-update (1)
checker.
.TP
.B Socket
AF_UNIX, newline-delimited JSON, bounded reads (4 KiB line cap, 5 s
timeout). Every connection is checked against
.B SO_PEERCRED
\(em only root or the configured
.I owner_uid
may issue commands \(em on top of the socket's own 0660 file mode. Two
independent gates.
.TP
.B Hostile input
Malformed JSON, non-objects, and unknown commands are answered with
.RI { \(dqerror\(dq : ...} and the connection ends; they never crash the
daemon.
.TP
.B The kill gate
Nothing is killed without a fresh, per-invocation confirmation typed at a
real TTY \(em no config flag, no persisting
.BR \-\-yes ,
no non-interactive kill path; a non-TTY stdin is refused outright by the
CLI before it ever reaches the socket. The daemon independently
re-validates
.RI ( pid ", " starttime )
identity against live
.I /proc
before signaling \(em a stale or reused pid is refused even if the CLI
layer were somehow bypassed. PID 1, kernel threads, and the daemon's own
pid are never valid targets, hardcoded, not configurable.
.TP
.B The memory.high floor
.I calm \-\-high
clamps its target to at least 1.1x the process's own current RSS \(em a
tampered or fat-fingered size can never be set low enough to
instant-thrash-OOM the process it's meant to calm.
.TP
.B Coexistence
If systemd-oomd or earlyoom is already active, every
.I calm
action and
.I advise
say so; RAMstein never races another OOM-fighter \(em its kill prompts
stay advisory information, not an automatic stand-down of the action
itself (that decision is still yours, and still requires the same TTY
confirmation).
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR ramstein (1),
.BR ramstein\-healthcheck (1),
